SIMPLE: polychromate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polychromate
<hw>Pol`y*chro"mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Polychromic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A salt of a
polychromic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polychromate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Polychromate
<hw>Pol`y*chro"mate</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Polychromatic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound which
exhibits, or from which may be prepared, a variety of colors, as certain
solutions derived from vegetables, which display colors by
fluorescence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polychromatic</ent>⟦br⟧
